											"content": [
												{
													"nodeType": "text",
													"data": {
														"target": null,
														"uri": null
													},
													"value": "Focus on the root cause, not the symptoms: ",
													"marks": [
														{
															"type": "bold"
														}
													],
													"content": null
												},
												{
													"nodeType": "text",
													"data": {
														"target": null,
														"uri": null
													},
													"value": "What's the single biggest challenge facing security teams today? Many teams can't agree on a focus area. Without that internal agreement, it's going to be difficult to meaningfully counter or prevent cyber threats, regardless of what security solution you buy. Too many security teams have fragmented approaches. Instead they need coordinated, comprehensive strategies that focus on root causes of attacks, not symptoms. For instance a concern over malware attachments is best addressed by eliminating the delivery mechanism, email phishing.  ",
													"marks": [],
													"content": null
